line_1: Oh vain enquiry! they without remorse
line_2: Are altogether gone a devious course,

line_1: Dumb, and convicted, but without remorse,
line_2: Faction was touch'd and felt the secret force,

line_1: "But not one grief was pointed by remorse;
line_2: " With joys, she'd griefs, had troubles in her course,
He clasped his daughter's pallid corse!

line_1: Whilst Raymond, fill'd with vain remorse,
The Critick else proceeds without Remorse,
line_2: Seizes your Fame, and puts his Laws in force.

line_1: "Her Head has he robb'd with as little Remorse
line_2: " As a Fox-Hunter crops both his Dogs and his Horse:
At eve the torrent stopt its course;

line_1: The guilty Soul with keen Remorse
line_2: Finds all his Gains repaid with Loss,
